defaultOur key finding was that the 
defaulthealth, safety and environmental risks associated with hydraulic fracturing as a means to extract shale gas can be managed effectively in the UK as long as operational best practices are 
defaultimplemented and enforced t
defaulthrough regulation. 
defaultHydraulic fracturing is an established technology that has been used in the oil and gas industries for many decades. 
defaultThe UK has 60 years’
default experience of regulating onshore and offshore oil and gas industries.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultWe were keen to stress that
default s
defaulthale gas extraction in the UK is presently at a very small scale, involving only exploratory activities. Uncertainties can be addressed through robust monitoring systems and research activities identified in this report. 
defaultThere is greater uncertainty abou
defaultt the scale
default of production activities should a future shale gas industry develop 
defaultnationwide
default.
default 
